In 2021, the COVID-19 pandemic swept through the globe, plunging the world into economic uncertainty. However, the Chinese economy remained largely resilient this year. In the first three quarters of 2021, China's economy grew by 9.8% year-on-year, higher than the expected target of more than 6%, and this resilience continued to show throughout the year.Â  In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh highlights China's economic performance for the year.